<worksheet label="ws-PA-poly-rational-features">
  <exploration xml:id="PA-poly-rational-features">
    <introduction>
      <p>
			Consider the rational function <m>r(x) = \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 - 3x - 4}</m>, and let <m>p(x) = x^2 - 1</m> (the numerator of <m>r(x)</m>) and <m>q(x) = x^2 - 3x - 4</m> (the denominator of <m>r(x)</m>).
		</p>
      <!--
		<figure xml:id="F-rational-features-hole-1">
			<caption>A plot of <m>r(x) = \frac{x^2 - 1}{x^2 - 3x - 4}</m>.</caption>
			<image source="images/rational-features-hole-1" width="60%" />
		</figure>
-->
      <p/>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-poly-rational-features-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p>
						Reasoning algebraically, for what values of <m>x</m> is <m>p(x) = 0</m>?
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution>
        <p>Factoring: <m>p(x) = x^2 - 1 = (x-1)(x+1)</m>.  So <m>p(x) = 0</m> when <m>x = 1</m> or <m>x = -1</m>.</p>
      </solution>
    </task>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="PA-poly-rational-features-task-1">
      <statement>
        <p>
						Again reasoning algebraically, for what values of <m>x</m> is <m>q(x) = 0</m>?
					</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer/>
      <solution>
        <p>Factoring: <m>q(x) = x^2 - 3x - 4 = (x-4)(x+1)</m>.  So <m>q(x) = 0</m> when <m>x = 4</m> or <m>x = -1</m>.</p>
      </solution>
    </task>
